<HEADLINE>
TAIWANESE FILM AWARDED IN BELGIUM
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Brussels, March 29 (CNA) 03/29/07  19:08:12 (By P.C. Tang and
Ruth Wang)
</P>
<P>
A Taiwanese movie titled "Three Times" and directed by Hou Hsiao
Hsien received the award of Best Film of 2006 in Belgium.
</P>
<P>
The award was given by a union of Belgian film critics at a
theater in Brussels Tuesday. Wang Cheng-tai, Information Division
chief under Taipei Representative Office to the European Union
and Belgium received the award on Hou's behalf.
</P>
<P>
The film tells three love stories in three different historical
times and stars local actors Chang Chen and Shu Qi.
</P>
<P>
The award was given for Hou's unique position in contemporary
film and for the film's exquisite cinematography and acting.
</P>
<P>
Wang expressed gratitude to the union and said he hopes for
cooperation between the Taiwanese and European film industries.
</P>
